node.text:
.
PURPLE AFGHANI KUSH S1
(Purple Afghani Kush x Purple Afghani Kush)
*feminized*
.
This lady is being beautifully grown outdoor by @stonerdave42047
.
Smell- Earthy with slight grape to floral undertones.
.
Flavor- She has smooth flavors of sweet floral earthiness and an undertone of grapes or mixed berries.
.
Appearance- She produces dense resinous purple buds with orange hair. She has dark green foliage, which begins turning purple to almost black half way through flower.
Some phenotypes keep green buds until nearly the end of flower, when they take on deep purple hues.
.
Effects- She is euphoric with a very relaxed calm high. She makes you feel uplifted, giggly, happy and creative. She is fantastic for controlling stress, anxiety and depression. She is wonderful for increasing appetite and helping with insomnia.
.

AGENT ORANGE 
(Orange Velvet x Jack The Ripper)

Agent Orange is a strain originally created by TGA Genetics.
We used my Orange Velvet clone only, Orange Skunk from Falls City Oregon and crossed her with Subcool’s(RIP) Jack the Ripper, a hybrid from Sub’s infamous Jack’s Cleaner crossed with TGAs well known Space Queen male aka Space Dude.

Agent Orange was named to honor my father.
He was an Army Green Beret Sergeant 1st class Vietnam Veteran.
He passed from cancer caused by his exposure to the chemical Agent Orange.

This stunning lady is being grown by @qualifirefarms .

She is described as being uplifting and motivating, a great mood enhancer if you are feeling lethargic or depressed. 
She has an aroma of fresh cut citrus with beautiful purple to deep maroon pigments.
Agent Orange is known to make wonderful orange concentrates.

I’m excited to say that Agent Orange will be making a comeback in 2022.
I am working on an Agent Orange line, which will also include a feminized version as well as several new Agent Orange hybrids. 

This Post is Intended for Educational and Entertainment Purposes Only.
